==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unseasonable
<hw>Un*sea"son*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
seasonable; being, done, or occurring out of the proper season;
ill-timed; untimely; too early or too late; <as>as, he called at an
<ex>unseasonable</ex> hour; <ex>unseasonable</ex> advice;
<ex>unseasonable</ex> frosts; <ex>unseasonable</ex> food.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Un*sea"son*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Un*sea"son*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unseasoned</ent>⟦br⟧
